# Unified Entry: `./ops`

All runnable capabilities in this repo are exposed through the **`./ops`** script at the repository root. Prefer `./ops` over calling scripts inside `scripts/` directly.

## Usage

```
./ops <capability-command> [options]
```

## Common Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `./ops test.kv_executor` | KV executor injection + source keyword audit |
| `./ops test.kv_executor --skip-build <build>` | Re-run without recompiling |
| `./ops test.brpc_kv_executor` | brpc/bthread reference cases + optional coverage |
| `./ops runtime.lock_perf` | Lock contention batch unit test |
| `./ops analysis.kv_executor_perf` | Executor inline vs injected curves / csv |
| `./ops analysis.collect_lock_baseline` | Gate + optional perf record to baseline dir |
| `./ops analysis.compare_lock_baseline` | Compare two run directories |
| `./ops analysis.lock_ebpf_workflow` | bpftrace workflow (prints sudo collection commands) |
| `./ops analysis.refresh_urma_index` | Generate URMA-aware index from compile_commands.json |
| `./ops docs.kv_observability_xlsx` | Generate observability workbook |

## Rules

- Only access `scripts/...` internal paths when **debugging or developing the scripts themselves**.
- If a capability is missing from `./ops`, add a route in `ops` and document it in `docs/agent/scripts-map.md`.
- When `DATASYSTEM_ROOT` is not set and the repos are not siblings, set it before running `./ops`.
